    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[Er92c] Erd\\H{o}s, P., Some of my forgotten problems in number theory. Hardy-Ramanujan J. (1992), 34-50.\n \n [ErPo80] P. Erd\\H{o}s and C. Pomerance, Matching the natural numbers up to $n$ with distinct multiples of another interval. Indigationes Math. (1980), 147-151.",
      "remarks": "A problem of Erd\\H{o}s and Pomerance \\cite{ErPo80}, who proved\\[(2/\\sqrt{e}+o(1))n\\left(\\frac{\\log n}{\\log\\log n}\\right)^{1/2}\\leq f(n)\\leq (1.7398\\cdots+o(1))n(\\log n)^{1/2}.\\]In \\cite{Er92c} Erd\\H{o}s offered 2000 rupees for an asymptotic formula; for uniform comparison across prizes I have converted this using the 1992 exchange rates.\n\nSee also [711]."
    },
